local function ReactorControl()
    local function redstone(state)
        if state then
            red.setOutput(sideRed, 15)
        else
            while red.getOutput(sideRed) > 0 or reactor.getReactorEUOutput() > 0 do
                red.setOutput(sideRed, 0)
                os.sleep(0.2)
            end
            gpu.setBackground(0x000000)
            gpu.setForeground(0x00FF00)
            gpu.set(1,14,"      eu/t =  0           ")
            gpu.setBackground(0x696969)
        end
    end
    local data = getInventory2(reactor)
    for i = 1,#slotReac do
        if data[slotReac[i]] then
            per = math.ceil(100*data[slotReac[i]].damage/data[slotReac[i]].maxDamage)
            gpu.setForeground(0xFF9900)
            gpu.set(tonumber(xy[slotReac[i]][1]),tonumber(xy[slotReac[i]][2]),tostring(per))
        else
            per = 0
        end
        if per == 100 then
            gpu.setBackground(0x000000)
            redstone(false)
            alert(" —Å–Ω–∏–∑—Ç–µ % –∑–∞–º–µ–Ω—ã –∫–æ–Ω–¥–µ–Ω—Å–∞—Ç. ")
            while run do
                computer.beep(500, 1)
                stop(3)
                gpu.setBackground(0x696969)
            end
            os.exit()
        end
        if per >= perDamage or per == 0 then
            gpu.setBackground(0x000000)
            gpu.setForeground(0xFF9900)
            gpu.set(1,15,"    –∑–∞–º–µ–Ω–∞ –∫–æ–Ω–¥–µ–Ω—Å–∞—Ç–æ—Ä–æ–≤    ")
            gpu.setBackground(0x696969)
            redstone(false)
            interface.pullItem("DOWN",slotReac[i])
            gpu.setForeground(0xFF0000)
            gpu.set(tonumber(xy[slotReac[i]][1]),tonumber(xy[slotReac[i]][2]),"‚ñà‚ñà")
            local data1 = getInventory(chest)
            for i1 = 1,slotsInv do
                if data1[i1] and data1[i1].name then
                    local per = math.ceil(100*data1[i1].damage/data1[i1].maxDamage)
                    if string.find(data1[i1].name,"ondensator") and per < 90 then
                        toReac = chest.pushItemIntoSlot("DOWN",i1,1,slotReac[i])
                        if toReac then
                            gpu.setForeground(0x696969)
                            gpu.setBackground(0x696969)
                            gpu.set(tonumber(xy[slotReac[i]][1]),tonumber(xy[slotReac[i]][2]),"‚ñà‚ñà")
                        end
                        break
                    else
                        toReac = 0
                    end
                end
            end
        end
    end
    local function circuitCheck()

        local data = getInventory2(reactor)
        local sh = 0
        for i = 1,#slotReac do
            if data[slotReac[i]] then
                sh = sh + 1
            end
        end
        if sh == #slotReac then
            return true
        else
            return false
        end
    end
    gpu.setBackground(0x000000)
    if reactor.getHeat() > offReac then
        redstone(false)
        alert("     –ø–µ—Ä–µ–≥—Ä–µ–≤ —Ä–µ–∞–∫—Ç–æ—Ä–∞ !    ")
    elseif not circuitCheck() then
        alert(" –Ω–µ—Ç —Ü–µ–ª—ã—Ö –∫–æ–Ω–¥–µ–Ω—Å–∞—Ç–æ—Ä–æ–≤ !  ")
    elseif toReac == 0 then
        alert("    –≤ —Å—É–Ω–¥—É–∫–µ –Ω–µ—Ç –º–µ—Å—Ç–∞ !   ")
    elseif noFuel >= 5 then
        alert("       –Ω–µ—Ç —Ç–æ–ø–ª–∏–≤–∞ !        ")
    else
        redstone(true)
        if not reactor.producesEnergy() then
            alert("  —Ä–µ–∞–∫—Ç–æ—Ä –Ω–µ –∑–∞–ø—É—Å–∫–∞–µ—Ç—Å—è !  ")
        else
            OutputEUt = math.ceil(reactor.getReactorEUOutput())

            gpu.set(1,14,"      eu/t =  "..OutputEUt.."            ")
            gpu.set(1,15,"      —Ä–µ–∞–∫—Ç–æ—Ä –∞–∫—Ç–∏–≤–µ–Ω       ")
        end
    end
    stop(0.7)
    gpu.setBackground(0x696969)
    if reactor.producesEnergy() and reactor.getReactorEUOutput() == 0 then
        noFuel = noFuel + 1
    else
        noFuel = 0
        if OutputEUt and OutputEUt < StartEUt then
            lowEu = lowEu + 1
        else
            lowEu = 0
        end
    end
    gpu.setBackground(0x000000)
    if noFuel == 3 or lowEu == 3 then
        local data2 = getInventory2(reactor)
        local data3 = getInventory(chest)
        for i2 = 1,54 do
            if data2[i2] and data2[i2].name then
                if string.find(data2[i2].name,"depleted") then
                    redstone(false)
                    gpu.setForeground(0xFF9900)
                    gpu.set(1,15,"      –∑–∞–º–µ–Ω–∞ —Å—Ç–µ—Ä–∂–Ω–µ–π       ")
                    interface.pullItem("DOWN",i2)
                    for i3 = 0,slotsInv do
                        if data3[i3] and data3[i3].name then
                            if string.find(data3[i3].name,"MOX") or string.find(data3[i3].name,"Uran") then
                                if not string.find(data3[i3].name,"depleted") then
                                    chest.pushItemIntoSlot("DOWN",i3,1,i2)
                                    break
                                end
                            end
                        end
                    end
                end
            end
        end
        StartEUt = 0
        lowEu = 0
        for i4 = 1,#Reflector do
            if not data2[Reflector[i4]] then
                for i5 = 0,slotsInv do
                    if data3[i5] and data3[i5].name then
                        if string.find(data3[i5].name,"eflector") then
                            redstone(false)
                            gpu.setForeground(0xFF9900)
                            gpu.set(1,15,"      –∑–∞–º–µ–Ω–∞ –æ—Ç—Ä–∞–∂–∞—Ç–µ–ª—è     ")
                            chest.pushItemIntoSlot("DOWN",i5,1,Reflector[i4])
                        end
                    end
                end
            end
        end
    end
    gpu.setBackground(0x696969)
    if OutputEUt and OutputEUt > StartEUt then
        StartEUt = math.ceil(reactor.getReactorEUOutput())
    end
end

gui()
gpu.setBackground(0x000000)
gpu.setForeground(0xFF9900)
gpu.set(1,14,"  –¥–ª—è –∑–∞–≤–µ—Ä—à–µ–Ω–∏—è –Ω–∞–∂–º–∏—Ç–µ E  ")
gpu.setBackground(0x696969)
os.sleep(1)
while run do
    local ok,err = pcall(ReactorControl)
    if not ok then
        red.setOutput(sideRed, 0)
        gpu.setResolution(w, h)
        gpu.setBackground(0x000000)
        gpu.setForeground(0xFFFFFF)
        os.execute("cls")
        print("–ø—Ä–æ–≥—Ä–∞–º–º–∞ –∞–≤–∞—Ä–∏–π–Ω–æ –∑–∞–≤–µ—Ä—à–µ–Ω–∞")
        if type(err) == "table" then
            io.stderr:write(table.unpack(err))
        else
            io.stderr:write(err)
        end
        run = false
    end
end

content:
size = 0
area = 0
bedrock = textutils.serialise("minecraft:bedrock")
shouldReturn = false
level = 0
sogliaFuel = 50
checkFuel = false

function Dig()
    local has_block, block = turtle.inspectDown()

    if has_block then
        blockType = textutils.serialise(block.name)
    
        if blockType == bedrock then
            return true
        end 

        turtle.digDown()
        return false

    end
end

function CalculateFuel()
    if (turtle.getFuelLevel() - level + area) > sogliaFuel == true then
        return true
    else
        return false
    end
end

print("-----------------------------")
print("\tBENVENUTO IN SCAVATORE 3000")
print("-----------------------------")

term.write("Inserisci dimensione: ")
size = read() - 1
area = size * size

turtle.refuel()

checkFuel = CalculateFuel()

if checkFuel == false then
    print("Carburante non sufficiente!")
else
    print("Perfetto, iniziamo!")
end

while (shouldReturn == false and checkFuel == true) do
    
    for r = 0, size do

        for c = 0, size do
            local digged = Dig()
    
            if digged == true then
                shouldReturn = true   
            end

            if c < size then
                turtle.forward()
            end
        end

        if r % 2 == 0 then
            turtle.turnRight()
            
            if r < size then
                turtle.forward()
            end
            
            turtle.turnRight()
        else
            turtle.turnLeft()
            
            if r < size then
                turtle.forward()
            end
            
            turtle.turnLeft()
        end

    end

    if level % 2 == 0 then
        checkFuel = CalculateFuel()
    end

    if shouldReturn == false then
        level = level + 1
        turtle.down()
    end

end

for y = 1, level do
    turtle.up()
end

title: text_skip_extractor
content:
#!/usr/bin/env python
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
# Filename: text_skip_extractor.py
# Version: 1.0.0
# Author: Jeoi Reqi

"""
Description:
    - This script extracts every 'n-th' letter from a text file, ignoring non-alphanumeric characters.
    - The user is prompted to select a file from the file manager and input a skip value.
    - The extracted letters are saved to a new file with a dynamically generated name based on the skip value.
    
Requirements:
    - Python 3.x
    - tkinter for file dialog

Functions:
    - extract_letters(text, skip):
        Extracts every 'skip' letter from the provided text.
    - main():
        Main function to execute the letter extraction process.

Usage:
    - Run the script in a Python environment with the following command:
    
                'python text_skip_extractor.py'
                
    - Follow the prompts to select a file and enter the skip value.

Example Output:

        Press Enter to open the file manager and select a file...

        Enter the shift value (positive integer): 7

        Extracted text:
                         THISWASATEST

        Extraction completed. The extracted letters are saved to shifted_7.txt.

                    Exiting Program...   GoodBye!

Additional Notes:
    - Ensure the file to be processed is a text file encoded in UTF-8.
    - The skip value should be a positive integer.
"""

import tkinter as tk
from tkinter import filedialog

def extract_letters(text, skip):
    """
    Extracts every 'skip' letter from the provided text, ignoring non-alphanumeric characters.
    
    Parameters:
    text (str): The input text from which letters are to be extracted.
    skip (int): The interval at which letters are extracted.
    
    Returns:
    str: A string containing every 'skip'th letter from the input text.
    """
    extracted = ""
    count = 0
    for char in text:
        if char.isalnum():  # Check if the character is alphanumeric
            count += 1
            if count % skip == 0:
                extracted += char
    return extracted

def main():
    """
    Main function to execute the letter extraction process:
        1. Prompts the user to open the file manager and select a text file.
        2. Reads the content of the selected file.
        3. Prompts the user to input a skip value.
        4. Extracts letters from the file content based on the skip value.
        5. Writes the extracted letters to a dynamically named file based on the skip value.
        6. Prints the extracted letters to the terminal.
    """
    # Prompt the user to hit Enter to open the file manager
    input("\nPress Enter to open the file manager and select a file...")

    # Open the file manager and let the user select a file
    root = tk.Tk()
    root.withdraw()  # Hide the main window
    file_path = filedialog.askopenfilename()

    # Check if a file was selected
    if not file_path:
        print("\nNo file selected!\n")
        return

    # Read the content of the selected file
    with open(file_path, 'r', encoding='UTF-8') as file:
        file_content = file.read()

    # Prompt the user to input the shift value
    skip_value = int(input("\nEnter the shift value (positive integer): "))

    # Extract letters based on the skip value, ignoring punctuation and spaces
    extracted_text = extract_letters(file_content, skip_value)

    # Dynamically generate the output filename based on the skip value
    output_filename = f"shifted_{skip_value}.txt"

    # Write the extracted letters to a new file
    with open(output_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as output_file:
        output_file.write(extracted_text)

    # Print the extracted text to the terminal
    print("\nExtracted text:\n\t\t", extracted_text)
    print(f"\nExtraction completed. The extracted letters are saved to {output_filename}.")
    print("\n\t\tExiting Program...   GoodBye!\n")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

TensorFlow Prediction Model
content:
import tensorflow as tf
from tensorflow.keras.datasets import mnist
from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential
from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense, Flatten
from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing import image
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Carregar o dataset MNIST
(xTreino, yTreino), (xTeste, yTeste) = mnist.load_data()
xTreino, xTeste = xTreino / 255.0, xTeste / 255.0

# Definir o modelo
modelo = Sequential([
    Flatten(input_shape=(28, 28)),
    Dense(128, activation='relu'),
    Dense(10, activation='softmax')
])

# Compilar o modelo
modelo.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])

# Treinar o modelo
modelo.fit(xTreino, yTreino, epochs=10)

# Avaliar o modelo
perda, acuracia = modelo.evaluate(xTeste, yTeste)
print(f'Perda: {perda}, Acur√°cia: {acuracia}')

# Fun√ß√£o para carregar e preparar uma nova imagem
def prepararImagem(caminhoArquivo):
    img = image.load_img(caminhoArquivo, color_mode='grayscale', target_size=(28, 28))
    img = image.img_to_array(img)
    img = np.expand_dims(img, axis=0)
    img = img / 255.0
    return img

# Fun√ß√£o para identificar o n√∫mero obtido
def identificarNumero(caminhoImagem):
    novaImagem = prepararImagem(caminhoImagem)
    previsao = modelo.predict(novaImagem)
    classePrevista = np.argmax(previsao, axis=1)[0]
    return classePrevista

# Carregar e testar uma nova imagem
caminhoNovaImagem = "numero.png"
novaImagem = prepararImagem(caminhoNovaImagem)

# Fazer a previs√£o
previsao = modelo.predict(novaImagem)
classePrevista = np.argmax(previsao, axis=1)

# Mostrar a imagem e a previs√£o
plt.imshow(novaImagem[0].reshape(28, 28), cmap='gray')
plt.title(f'Classe prevista: {classePrevista[0]}')
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()

#imprimir o n√∫mero identificado
print("O n√∫mero identificado na imagem √©: ",classePrevista)
